  "commentary": "With SPX at 6931.56 sitting between the 6925 (+6.25B) and 6950 (+15.4B) gamma walls in a PIN regime, dealers are positioned to sell any push toward the massive 6950 resistance level while providing support on dips toward 6900 (+8.7B). The dense positive gamma structure from 6900-7000 creates a strong mean-reverting environment where rallies face increasing dealer selling pressure and dips get bought. Key levels to watch are the 6950 max gamma strike as the primary resistance and 6900 as the lower bound of the current consolidation range, with the GEX flip at 6857 marking where dealer behavior would shift if breached.\n\nBottom line: expect sideways chop between 6900-6950 with limited breakout potential.",
